<node CREATED="1153994894333" ID="Freemind_Link_1415219224" MODIFIED="1153995201199" TEXT="From David Martin&apos;s Email">
<hook NAME="accessories/plugins/NodeNote.properties">
<text>NOMCOM Process Document&#xa;Version 0.2&#xa;David E. Martin martinde@us.ibm.com&#xa;&#xa;The Open Grid Forum has established the Nominating Committee (NOMCOM) process to evaluate and recommend candidates for leadership positions in the OGF. The NOMCOM process is inherited from the IETF&#x2019;s process ad described in RFC3777. The purpose and intend are the same,. Due to the different structure of the OGF the implementation differs and those differences are described in this document.&#xa;&#xa;There are four distinct groups in the GGF leadership:&#xa;Area Directors &#x2013; Area Directors are responsible for management and development of a specific topic or area in OGF.&#xa;Vice Presidents &#x2013; OGF vice presidents are responsible for management and development of major functions of OGF, currently Enterprise Community, Research Community, Standards and Operations.&#xa;GGF President and CEO &#x2013; The President is responsible for overall management and development of OGF.&#xa;Board Members &#x2013; 2/3 or the board seats are filled by an election by the Platinum members.  The NOMCOM has no responsibility for these.  The other 1/3 of the board members are At Large and are intended to represent the general OGF community.&#xa;&#xa;The NOMCOM process for each of these is slightly different.  &#xa;&#xa;Nominations&#xa;With the exception of board positions, any OGF member may nominate any OGF member, including themselves, for any open position.  An OGF member may make any number of nominations and may nominate the same nominee for multiple positions and multiple nominees for the same position.  &#xa;[Q from Cees: should we restrict to only OGF members?]&#xa;&#xa;There are two types of board positions, sponsor and at-large.  Sponsor positions are handled by the Platinum members.  For at-large positions, any OGF member may nominate any number of OGF members as long as the nominee&#x2019;s organization is not already represented on the board.&#xa;[Q from Cees: I need some help here. i am reading the bylaws which were attached to a mail from Mark on 2nd of June to GFSG to prepare for vote for merger.  3.1 definitions said: 3.1 At-Large Members.   &#xa;This describes the combined group of members comprised of Tier 2 and Tier 3 Organizational members and the Individual class of members. &#xa;Also one can read the text in the bylaws as: anyone can submit nominee names for at large seats, anyone being member, but not student and not from tier 1 organisation already on board, can be nominee. NOMCOM makes candidate list, tier one votes the at large out of this candidate list&#xa;&#xa;I changed the text above to be &#x201c;any OGF member may nominate&#x201d;]&#xa;&#xa;Evaluation&#xa;1.&#x9;The NOMCOM will determine which nominees are willing to accept the nomination.&#xa;2.&#x9;The NOMCOM will discuss the requirements for the open positions with the GGF leadership (board, president, vice presidents, area directors).&#xa;3.&#x9;The NOMCOM will evaluate all of those willing to serve, often through in-person interviews.&#xa;4.&#x9;The NOMCOM will keep all information confidential.&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;Proposed Slate&#xa;For Area Directors, the NOMCOM will present a list of open positions and a single candidate for each to the OGF Board for confirmation.&#xa;For vice presidents, the NOMCOM will present a list of all highly-qualified candidates to the president.  The president will interview, evaluate and choose a single candidate for each position to be presented to the board. The board will confirm the candidate.&#xa;For the President and CEO, the NOMCOM will present a list of all highly-qualified candidates to the board.&#xa;For at large board members, the NOMCOM will present a list of highly-qualified candidates to the board, with the restriction that only one candidate is allowed from each organization and no candidate is allowed from organizations that are already represented on the board.&#xa;&#xa;Election&#xa;For Area Directors, the Gold and Platinum sponsors vote to either accept or reject the entire slate.  If the slate is rejected, the NOMCOM has the choice of presenting a new slate or starting the NOMCOM process over. In case of rejection, the board has to explain its decision to the NOMCOM in writing.&#xa;For Vice Presidents, the Gold and Platinum sponsors vote to either accept or reject the slate proposed by the President.  If the slate is rejected, the President may propose a different slate or start the NOMCOM process over.&#xa;For the President and CEO, the board will interview and evaluate the candidates.  They will then vote the candidates. [need voting mechanism here].  &#xa;For At Large board members, the Platinum and Gold sponsors will vote to fill the open positions.  &#xa;&#xa;[need voting mechanism here.]&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;</text>
</hook>
</node>
